title: Interview with Michimasa Hirata
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: In this five-part oral history Michimasa (Michi) Hirata discusses his life and activism, centered on his survival of the Hiroshima atomic bomb on August 6, 1945. Part 1: Background, Early Life, WWII, Hiroshima. Part 2: Hiroshima, End of WWII. Part 3: Occupied Japan, Press Code, Education. Part 4: Professional Career, Family, Activism. Part 5: Activism, Reflections.
